<p>
	Incense resin is the oldest form of incense. The use of tree resin as an aromatic substance can be traced back to more than six thousand years ago and is a highly effective alternative to the other options available. &nbsp;</p>
<p>
	This type of incense is what chapels and temples around the world first used. Resin incense requires charcoal to burn so care must be taken at all times. Although resin incense is more complicated and time consuming than cones and sticks, it is the most ancient way to experience the aromas and feels more authentic. &nbsp;</p>
